    • Method Detail

      • getSwimlanePos

        public int getSwimlanePos()
        Gets the current position of the represented swimlane.

        The swimlane positions are described by a zero-based index and must not be negative.

        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the position is smaller than 0
        Returns:
        the current position of the swimlane
        See Also:
        setSwimlanePos(int)

      • isRearrangementAllowed

        public boolean isRearrangementAllowed()
        Gets whether or not the represented swimlane can be rearranged.

        For all swimlanes with disabled rearrangement, the relative ordering given by SwimlanePos is preserved. The other swimlanes may be rearranged.

        Returns:
        true if the represented swimlane can be rearranged, false otherwise
        See Also:
        setRearrangementAllowed(boolean)

      • setRearrangementAllowed
